ble></div>")
    SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "E", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Commercial", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], renovation: false)), name: "Energy Use Performance"), name: "APPLICABILITY", display_weight: 1, visible: true, html_text: "<p>COMMERCIAL | EDUCATION | HOMES | HOSPITALITY | LIGHT INDUSTRY | MOSQUES | OFFICES | RESIDENTIAL</p>")
    SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "E", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Commercial", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], renovation: false)), name: "Energy Use Performance"), name: "ASSESSMENT PRINCIPLES", display_weight: 3, visible: true, html_text: "<ul><li>The Project will <span>assess</span> GSAS energy performance coefficient of the energy use (EPCuse) in relation to applicable GSAS benchmark.</li><li>The Project will complete <span>GSAS Energia Suite&trade;</span> for E.2 Energy Use Performance to establish the <span>criterion level</span>.</li></ul>")
    SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "E", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Commercial", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], renovation: false)), name: "Energy Use Performance"), name: "ASSESSMENT", display_weight: 4, visible: true, html_text: "<p>The criterion requires <span>assessing</span> the annual energy use of the building by calculating the EPC value using <span>GSAS Energia Suite&trade;</span>.  Based on occupancy, operations profile and building type, the assessment considers the energy use associated with the design of the following building systems:</p><p>-\tCooling systems based on seasonal energy efficiency ratio (SEER) or coefficient of performance (COP). </p><p>-\tLighting system and controls.</p><p>-\tAuxiliary systems comprising of ventilation system, air supply system, and HVAC pump system.</p><p>-\tDomestic hot water system</p><p>-\tEnergy generation systems, such as photovoltaic (PV), solar hot water, wind turbine, absorption chiller, and combined heat and power (CHP).</p><p><span>GSAS</span><span> </span><span>Energia</span> <span>Suite&trade;</span> determines for each building type, the energy performance coefficient (EPC<span>use</span>) based on the aspects of the building systems design.</p><div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td rowspan=\"2\"><p><span>EPC</span><span>use</span></p></td><td rowspan=\"2\"><p><span>=</span></p></td><td><p><span>E</span><span>use_norm</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span>E</span><span>use_ref</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table></div><p>Where:</p><p>EPC<span>use</span> \tis the energy use performance coefficient.</p><p>E<span>use_norm</span> \tis the normalized energy use in kWh/m<span>2</span>/yr.</p><p>E<span>use_ref</span> \tis GSAS benchmark for the energy use.  It is the reference energy of the notional building for a specific building type in kWh/m<span>2</span>/yr.</p><p><br/>The <span>criterion level</span> is established based on the result of the EPC<span>use</span>.</p>")
