    SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "MO", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Commercial", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], renovation: false)), name: "Automated Control System"), name: "ASSESSMENT", display_weight: 4, visible: true, html_text: "<p>The criterion requires <span>assessing</span> the system of automated controls for the energy and water systems of the facility by preparing an automated control system plan.  The energy systems of the facility for assessment of its automated controls include the air-conditioning and ventilation systems and the lighting system.  The water system of the facility for assessment of its automated controls includes the irrigation system only.</p><p>The automated control system <span>plan</span> is a document that outlines the development&rsquo;s plan for a system of automated controls and monitoring of the operational performance of the listed energy and water systems from above.  </p><p>The plan demonstrates the following requirements:</p><ul><li>Provision of a system for the automated controls and monitoring of the energy and water systems of the facility. </li><li>Layouts, schematics, sequence of operations, and specifications to understand the functionalities of the provided automated control system.</li><li>Training schedules and modules for the facility management personnel on the proper operations and maintenance of the control system.</li><li>Handover documents for the facility management.</li></ul>")
