    SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "MO", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Education", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], renovation: false)), name: "Facility Management"), name: "ASSESSMENT", display_weight: 4, visible: true, html_text: "<p>The criterion requires <span>assessing</span> the best practices adopted for the operational management of the facility and the upkeep of the property assets of the development by preparing a facility management plan.</p><p>The facility management <span>plan</span> is a document that outlines the sustainable approach to the strategic management process for operating and maintaining a facility.  A sustainable approach indicates there is a comprehensive model followed for strategic planning.  </p><p>The plan demonstrates the following requirements:</p><ul><li>Provisions required for proper housekeeping of the development operations including janitorial, help desk support, storing facility, security, etc. </li><li>Provisions required for proper operation and maintenance of the development including building maintenance unit, access control, surveillance, MEP associated services, etc. </li></ul>")
