    SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "UC", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Hospitality", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], renovation: false)), name: "Public Transportation"), name: "ASSESSMENT PRINCIPLES", display_weight: 3, visible: true, html_text: "<ul><li>The Project will <span>assess</span> the availability of public transportation stops or stations within specified distance ranges.</li><li>The Project will complete the <span>calculator</span> for UC.4 Public Transportation to establish the <span>criterion level</span>.</li></ul>")
    SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "UC", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Hospitality", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], renovation: false)), name: "Public Transportation"), name: "ASSESSMENT", display_weight: 4, visible: true, html_text: "<p>The criterion requires <span>assessing</span> the availability of public transportation stops or stations by counting the number of public bus stops and rail or metro stations within the specified distance ranges from the accessible entrances of the development site.  The specified distance ranges are within the 500m, 750m, and 1,000m distances. The existing and planned locations of the public bus stops and rail or metro stations are as shown in the official maps of the Center for Geographic Information System (CGIS) or from other official transit guide maps from the transportation planning department.</p><p>The <span>calculator</span> determines the indicator based on the average weighted-quantities of the public bus stops, rail or metro stations within the specified distance ranges from the site entrance.</p><p>The <span>criterion level</span> is established based on the result of the indicator for UC.4 Public Transportation.</p>")
    SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "UC", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Hospitality", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], renovation: false)), name: "Public Transportation"), name: "CRITERION LEVELS", display_weight: 5, visible: true, html_text: "<div class=\"table-responsive\"><table class=\"table table-bordered\"><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody><tr><td><p><span>Levels</span></p></td><td><p><span>Public Transportation (X) Indicator</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span>0</span></p></td><td><p>X &lt; 2</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span>1</span></p></td><td><p>2 <span>&le;</span> X &lt; 4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span>2</span></p></td><td><p>4 <span>&le;</span> X &lt; 6</p></td></tr><tr><td><p><span>3</span></p></td><td><p>X &ge; 6</p></td></tr></tbody></table></div>")
    SchemeCriterionText.create!(scheme_criterion: SchemeCriterion.find_by(scheme_category: SchemeCategory.find_by(code: "UC", scheme: Scheme.find_by(name: "Hospitality", gsas_document: "GSAS Building Typologies_Assessment_2019_14.html", gsas_version: "2019", certificate_type: Certificate.certificate_types[:design_type], renovation: false)), name: "Public Transportation"), name: "EVALUATION", display_weight: 7, visible: true, html_text: "<ol><li>General<ul><li>Use a site map to determine the total number of public bus stops and rail or metro stations that are within the specified actual walking distance ranges of 500m, 750m, and 1,000m.  The number of bus stops includes the number of bus routes the stop serves.</li><li>Input the quantities of the public bus stops and rail or metro stations per distance range into the calculator for UC.4 Public Transportation to determine the Public Transportation indicator.</li><li>Prepare all applicable documentation.</li></ul></li><li>Calculator<p>A. Inputs</p><ul><li>Input the quantity of the public bus stops and rail or metro stations that are within 500m, 750m, and 1,000m distances from the main entrances of the site.</li></ul><p>B. Calculations</p><ul><li>Weights = fixed values (ranging from 1 to 6) assigned to give relative importance for the calculations of performance value for public bus stops and rail or metro stations that are within the specified distances.</li><li>(X) = calculated value based on the average weighted-quantities of the public bus stops and rail or metro stations that are within the specified distance ranges from the site entrance.</li><li>UC.4 criterion level = the generated criterion level for UC.4 Public Transportation based on the specified range from the criterion levels.</li></ul></li></ol>")
